  <mads:note type="nonpublic">The authorship of the 2nd collection of the Imagines has sometimes
      been attributed to this author, but the majority of Classical scholarship still seems to
      attribute this work to Philostratus the Lemnian, 3rd cent</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">Wikipedia, June 4, 2007: (Philostratus IV; b. ca. 220)</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">Flinterman, Jaap-Jan. Power, paideia &amp; Pythagoreanism, 1995: p.
      11 (W. Schmid atrributes the 2nd collection of the Imagines to a son of Philostratus III and
      the daughter of Philostratus II, known as Philostratus IV, but this view is debated)</mads:note>
